HEADWORD: Inhumanity
<hw>In`hu*man"i*ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Inhumanities</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.
<ets>inhumanitas</ets>: cf. F. <ets>inhumanit⟦eacute⟧</ets>.]</ety>
<def>The quality or state of being inhuman or inhumane; cruelty;
barbarity.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Man's <qex>inhumanity</qex> to man⟦br⟧
